Create a function in ~/.bashrc   :

function set-title() {
  if [[ -z "$ORIG" ]]; then
    ORIG=$PS1
  fi
  TITLE="\[\e]2;$*\a\]"
  PS1=${ORIG}${TITLE}
}
Then use your new command to set the terminal title. It works with spaces in the name too

set-title my new tab title
need restart
